 Position 
This position has a high degree of visibility with senior executives within the Company and within the financial community. The successful candidate will help develop and execute a strategically focused investor relations program and have the ability to impact the Companyâ€™s financial strategy and messaging. 
 
Reporting to the Vice President of Investor Relations, this person will become a key spokesperson and liaison for the sell-side and buy-side communities. This position will work with executive, finance, product, strategy, legal and marketing teams to analyze, strategize and develop high-impact messages. 
Responsibilities will include: 
Cultivation and development of relationships within the investment and analyst communities. 
Analysis of business and financial fundamentals of the company and its competitors/peers. 
Valuation comparisons across EDA and other relevant industries. 
Partner with VP in preparation of earnings scripts, Q&As, supplemental financial documents and corporate presentations 
Review SEC filings; take part in Disclosure Committee. 
Help in educating company representatives about disclosure (Reg FD and others) parameters and cautions. 
Partner with department to develop and deploy proactive targeting strategy. 
Help the team in coordinating events, prep sessions, speaker coaching, conference logistics/materials, etc. 
Partner with other areas of the CFO organization to help drive corporate financial strategy and execution. 
Some travel required. 
Preferred Skills/Experience 
Solid analytical skills and business judgment. Solid understanding of finance and investments. 
At least 10 years of experience in a related role such as investor relations, fund management/analysis, financial planning and analysis, sell-side analysis, treasury, and/or accounting (broad-based; SEC reporting). 
An outstanding reputation of credibility, strategic thinking, depth and breadth of understanding and complete, thoughtful and accurate work products. 
A successful track record managing both internal and external relationships. Ability to develop and maintain effective working relationships across organizational boundaries. 
A demonstrated ability to interact with professionals in various functional areas. Identify conflicting messages throughout the organization. Drive resolution via tactful influence. 
Outstanding oral and written communication and presentation skills. Influential, organized and articulate. 
Proactive and hands-on manager, willing to get deeply involved in all aspects of Investor Relations, both strategically and tactically. 
The ability to work under pressure and a poised and capable demeanor. 
Investor Relations experience is helpful, but not required, if there is a demonstrated interest in investments and/or Wall Street. 
Bachelorâ€™s degree in Finance/Accounting or equivalent experience. CFA and/or MBA or other related Masterâ€™s degree preferred. 
Security and/or software industry experience preferred. 
